    "headline": "Goldman Sachs Retirement Survey 2025: Retirement Could Cost $2.5 Million by 2043, and Most Americans Are Not Saving Fast Enough to Keep Up",
    "summary": "The Goldman Sachs Retirement Survey & Insights Report 2025 puts a hard number on what many workers already sense: the bar for retirement keeps moving higher. The estimated total cost of retirement for a unisex retiree is projected to reach $2,569,000 by 2043, up from $1,747,000 in 2033. That climb reflects two forces working together. ... Goldman Sachs Retirement Survey 2025: Retirement Could Cost $2.5 Million by 2043, and Most Americans Are Not Saving Fast Enough to Keep Up",
